# Shared data store (vislab-common/data). Keep the small calibration/derived .mat
# files in git (so a fresh clone can run the colour transforms), but ignore the
# large image/texture datasets -- those are obtained separately / synced via OneDrive.
# (GitHub rejects files >100 MB.) Default to ignoring, then re-include small .mat files:
/data/*
!/data/*.mat
# ...except the ~3.7 GB derived CDFs, which is too large for git:
/data/nat_im_cdfs.mat
